Cat 1 Light Purple (Werewolf) - Light purple evokes romantic and nostalgic feelings. In this specific scene, Ethan is looking at his boyfriend whom you can tell he loves very, very much. Cat 2 Dark Red (Telekinetic) - Dark red is associated with rage, anger, courage, longing, malice and wrath. This connects to Carrie because she slowly opens up through the movie and gains courage and longs to be like the other girls and by the end of the movie in a fit of rage and embarrassment kills her classmates after being pranked at the prom. Cat 3 Black (Deadite) - Black is associated with power, death, evil and mystery. In the Evil Dead series, deadites are evil spirits who possess the living. Cat 4 Red Orange (Demon) - Red-orange corresponds to desire, dominance, aggression and thirst for action. In Supernatural, Abaddon takes action against Crowley to overthrow him and become Queen of Hell. Cat 5 Pink (Goddess) - Pink signifies romance, love and friendship, it's also associated with with feminine qualities. Aphrodite is the goddess of love and isn't afraid to show her feminine side. *credit is a must *do not alter without permission *comments are appreciated *Texture credit post

Extras
These all come from my Tarot deck, which I used instead of the websites. - The Tower: Chaos, ruin, adversity, upheaval. In the show, Danny has been seen in the midst of chaos more than once. - Eight of Swords: Inner conflict and turmoil. Bound by fears, blind to the truth. Through the season we were lead to believe that Danny didn't know about the supernatural, so I 'blinded' him in the icon. - Queen of Wands: She reveals her power of observation and leadership. Affability, growth, development, passion. We have seen on multiple occasions that Danny is highly intelligent and very observant. Especially in the 3B finale, where he reveals that he does in fact know about werewolves. - Two of Cups: Friendship, balance, partnership, sharing, understanding. Danny is Jackson's best friend. So I put the two of them together, and I thought the screencap was fitting seeing as they were both holding cups. - Ace of Cups: Intimacy, fertility, beginnings, openness, insight, abundance. In this scene not only do we see Danny and Ethan being intimate, but you see Danny opening up about his past. *credit is a must *do not alter without permission *comments are appreciated *Texture credit post
